    {
      "id": "d4e5f6a7-b8c9-4d0e-1f2a-3b4c5d6e7f8a",
      "step": 4,
      "question": "What will this function return?",
      "codeSnippet": "function multiply(a, b) {\n  a * b;\n}\nconsole.log(multiply(2, 5));",
      "correctAnswerId": "8l9m0n1o-2p3q-4r4s-5t6u-7v8w9x0y1z2a",
      "explanation": "If a function doesn't have an explicit 'return' statement, it returns 'undefined' by default, even if an expression is evaluated inside.",
