        { "id": "2t3u4v5w-6x7y-4z8a-9b0c-1d2e3f4g5h6i", "text": "Hi name" },
        { "id": "3u4v5w6x-7y8z-4a9b-0c1d-2e3f4g5h6i7j", "text": "Hi undefined" },
        { "id": "4v5w6x7y-8z9a-4b0c-1d2e-3f4g5h6i7j8k", "text": "Error" },
        { "id": "5w6x7y8z-9a0b-4c1d-2e3f-4g5h6i7j8k9l", "text": "Hi " }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "a2b3c4d5-e6f7-4a8b-9c0d-1e2f3a4b5c6d",
      "step": 13,
      "question": "Can a function return another function?",
      "codeSnippet": null,
      "correctAnswerId": "6x7y8z9a-0b1c-4d2e-3f4g-5h6i7j8k9l0m",
      "explanation": "Yes, functions are 'first-class citizens' in JavaScript, meaning they can be treated like any other value, including being returned from other functions (often called Higher-Order Functions).",
      "answers": [
        { "id": "6x7y8z9a-0b1c-4d2e-3f4g-5h6i7j8k9l0m", "text": "Yes" },
        { "id": "7y8z9a0b-1c2d-4e3f-4g5h-6i7j8k9l0m1n", "text": "No, only primitives" },
        { "id": "8z9a0b1c-2d3e-4f4g-5h6i-7j8k9l0m1n2o", "text": "No, only objects" },
        { "id": "9a0b1c2d-3e4f-4g5h-6i7j-8k9l0m1n2o3p", "text": "Only if it is a method" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "d7e8f9a0-b1c2-4d3e-4f5a-6b7c8d9e0f1a",
      "step": 14,
      "question": "What is 'arguments' inside a non-arrow function?",
      "codeSnippet": null,
      "correctAnswerId": "1c2d3e4f-5g6h-4i7j-8k9l-0m1n2o3p4q5r",
      "explanation": "The 'arguments' object is an array-like object accessible inside functions. It has a 'length' property and indexed elements, but lacks built-in Array methods like map() or filter().",
      "answers": [
        { "id": "0b1c2d3e-4f5g-4h6i-7j8k-9l0m1n2o3p4q", "text": "A true Array" },
        { "id": "1c2d3e4f-5g6h-4i7j-8k9l-0m1n2o3p4q5r", "text": "An array-like object" },
        { "id": "2d3e4f5g-6h7i-4j8k-9l0m-1n2o3p4q5r6s", "text": "A string" },
        { "id": "3e4f5g6h-7i8j-4k9l-0m1n-2o3p4q5r6s7t", "text": "A list of global variables" },
        { "id": "4f5g6h7i-8j9k-4l0m-1n2o-3p4q5r6s7t8u", "text": "Undefined" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "f4a5b6c7-d8e9-4f0a-1b2c-3d4e5f6a7b8c",
      "step": 15,
      "question": "What is the output of the following?",
      "codeSnippet": "function check(a) {\n  return a || 'Default';\n}\nconsole.log(check(0));",
      "correctAnswerId": "6h7i8j9k-0l1m-4n2o-3p4q-5r6s7t8u9v0w",
      "explanation": "The logical OR (||) operator returns the first truthy value. Since 0 is falsy in JavaScript, the operator evaluates and returns the second operand: 'Default'.",
      "answers": [
        { "id": "5g6h7i8j-9k0l-4m1n-2o3p-4q5r6s7t8u9v", "text": "0" },
        { "id": "6h7i8j9k-0l1m-4n2o-3p4q-5r6s7t8u9v0w", "text": "'Default'" },
        { "id": "7i8j9k0l-1m2n-4o3p-4q5r-6s7t8u9v0w1x", "text": "undefined" },
        { "id": "8j9k0l1m-2n3o-4p4q-5r6s-7t8u9v0w1x2y", "text": "true" },
        { "id": "9k0l1m2n-3o4p-4q5r-6s7t-8u9v0w1x2y3z", "text": "null" },
        { "id": "0l1m2n3o-4p5q-4r6s-7t8u-9v0w1x2y3z4a", "text": "NaN" }
      ]
    }
  ]
